        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued March 27 at 5:36PM CDT by NWS Corpus Christi TX</headline>
        <description>At 535 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Riviera, or near Sarita, moving north at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Riviera Beach, Bishop, Loyola Beach, Riviera, Ricardo, Kingsville
Naval Air Station, Driscoll, and Kingsville.

This includes US Highway 77 between mile markers 680 and 708.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
